title: Cheat-Sheet Variable
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Variables can be defined with [[macro definitions|Cheat-Sheet MDefinition]], or the widgets `<$set ...>`, `<$vars ...>` or `<$let ...>`. For ''new code'' use the ''let-widget'', because it is the latest. 

This example uses the set-widget so the cheat-sheet can also be used with old wikis.

For example:

<$set name="targetTiddler" value="Cheat-Sheet Variable">
  <$button message="tm-navigate" to=<<targetTiddler>> >Open tiddler: <<targetTiddler>></$button>
</$set>
